    <description>This is a Screen Flow.
Upon initiation, the flow retrieves the input Knowledge Article record. It then checks the article&apos;s publication status. If the article is published, it looks for existing drafts. If a draft exists and is newer, it displays the draft&apos;s content for summarization. If no draft exists or the user wants to create a new one, a new draft is created from the published article. The flow then generates a summary using AI and allows the user to edit it. Finally, it saves the summary to the Knowledge Article and displays a success message.

Several objects and their fields worth mentioning. Below are the details (the format is given as: object_name - field_name: interaction)
  * [&apos;Knowledge__kav&apos;, &apos;Id, KnowledgeArticleId, Title, Answer__c, PublishStatus, CreatedDate, ArticleCreatedDate&apos;]
  * [&apos;Knowledge__kav&apos;, &apos;Summary&apos;]</description>
